main event: A civilian woman reported seeing a bright orange circular object hovering over the Philadelphia International Airport on April 9, 1966.
interesting points: The object was larger than the visual image of the sun and hovered for approximately 5 minutes.
Another witness, Mrs. Robert Curran, also reported seeing a similar bright orange circular object in the sky that same night.
Mrs. Curran said the object had a red light in the center and a white light in the back, and that the lights seemed to be blinking on and off.
The sighting lasted around 10 minutes and the object seemed to drop suddenly in a spotlight fashion.
The Air Force investigated the sightings but could not determine the identity of the objects.
witnesses: Miss Regina McFadden, Mrs. Robert Curran
